{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "briapi-sit-validator-collection",
    "name": "BRIAPI SIT Validator",
    "description": "Collection for testing the BRIAPI SIT Validator service.\n\nThis service validates Excel files submitted by BRIAPI partners as part of the System Integration Testing (SIT) process. It checks that all test case rows in the file have been properly filled in (Request, Response, Result, Notes).\n\n## Recommended Workflow\n1. **POST /api/v1/sheets** — upload the SIT file and get back the list of available sheet names.\n2. Choose which sheets you want to validate.\n3. **POST /api/v1/validate** — upload the file again with a `sheets` form field containing the chosen sheet names.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection into Postman.\n2. Import the `BRIAPI_SIT_Validator.postman_environment.json` environment file.\n3. Select the **BRIAPI SIT Validator — Local** environment.\n4. Set the `sit_file_path` environment variable to the absolute path of your `.xlsx` SIT file.\n5. Run the server locally: `go run -mod=vendor ./cmd/server`\n\n## Endpoints\n- `GET  /api/v1/health`   — Health check\n- `POST /api/v1/sheets`   — List available sheet names in the uploaded file\n- `POST /api/v1/validate` — Validate a SIT Excel file (JSON or Excel output)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 — Health",
      "description": "Check that the service is running and get the current version.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "{{api_version}}", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Returns HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\", \"version\": \"1.0.0\"}` when the service is running."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                {"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json; charset=utf-8"}
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has status ok', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has version field', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.version).to.be.a('string');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 — Discover Sheets",
      "description": "Upload a SIT Excel file and get back the list of available product sheet names. Use this to discover which sheets exist before calling /validate with a specific filter.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Sheets in File",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Request-ID",
                "value": "postman-{{$randomUUID}}",
                "description": "Optional. If omitted the service generates one automatically."
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "{{sit_file_path}}",
                  "description": "The SIT Excel file (.xlsx). Set sit_file_path in the environment."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sheets",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "{{api_version}}", "sheets"]
            },
            "description": "Returns a JSON array of all product sheet names in the uploaded workbook, excluding administrative sheets (e.g. Changelog, Daftar Isi) that are configured to be skipped.\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"sheets\": [\n    \"Interbank Transfer\",\n    \"QR MPM\",\n    \"Virtual Account\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nUse the returned names to populate the `sheets` field in /validate requests."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 — Sheet list",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                {"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json; charset=utf-8"}
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"sheets\": [\n    \"Interbank Transfer\",\n    \"QR MPM\",\n    \"Virtual Account\",\n    \"DirectDebit\",\n    \"SNAP BI\"\n  ]\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has sheets array', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.sheets).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Sheet names are strings', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    json.sheets.forEach(function(s) {",
                  "        pm.expect(s).to.be.a('string');",
                  "    });",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Store the first sheet name so the next request can use it as a default filter.",
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.sheets && json.sheets.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('discovered_sheets', json.sheets.join(','));",
                  "    pm.environment.set('sheet_filter', json.sheets[0]);",
                  "    console.log('Available sheets: ' + json.sheets.join(', '));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 — Validate (JSON response)",
      "description": "Upload a SIT Excel file and receive a structured JSON validation report.\n\nYou can choose which sheets to validate by supplying a `sheets` form field in the request body (comma-separated sheet names). Alternatively, pass `sheets` as a query string parameter. If omitted, all product sheets are validated.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Validate — All Sheets (JSON)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Request-ID",
                "value": "postman-{{$randomUUID}}",
                "description": "Optional. If omitted the service generates one automatically."
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "{{sit_file_path}}",
                  "description": "The SIT Excel file (.xlsx). Set sit_file_path in the environment."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/validate",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "{{api_version}}", "validate"]
            },
            "description": "Validates all product sheets in the uploaded file.\n\nReturns a JSON report with:\n- `status`: `\"ok\"` or `\"incomplete\"`\n- `summary`: global counts (total sheets, OK/incomplete)\n- `sheets[]`: per-sheet metadata status and test case results"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 — Incomplete (example)",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                {"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json; charset=utf-8"}
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"incomplete\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"total_sheets\": 23,\n    \"sheets_ok\": 18,\n    \"sheets_incomplete\": 5,\n    \"total_test_cases\": 187,\n    \"test_cases_ok\": 160,\n    \"test_cases_incomplete\": 27\n  },\n  \"sheets\": [\n    {\n      \"sheet_name\": \"Interbank Transfer\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"provider_name\": { \"value\": \"PT Bank XYZ\", \"status\": \"ok\" },\n        \"partner_name\":  { \"value\": \"\",            \"status\": \"missing\" },\n        \"test_date\":     { \"value\": \"2025-03-01\",  \"status\": \"ok\" }\n      },\n      \"summary\": { \"total\": 13, \"ok\": 10, \"incomplete\": 3 },\n      \"test_cases\": [\n        {\n          \"no\": \"8.1\",\n          \"service\": \"Any Service\",\n          \"scenario\": \"Access Token Invalid\",\n          \"status\": \"incomplete\",\n          \"issues\": [\n            \"Request belum diisi (harus berupa curl: URL Endpoint, Header Request, Request Body)\",\n            \"Response Body belum diisi\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"no\": \"8.2\",\n          \"service\": \"Any Service\",\n          \"scenario\": \"Unauthorized . Signature\",\n          \"status\": \"ok\",\n          \"issues\": []\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has status field', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.be.oneOf(['ok', 'incomplete']);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has summary object', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.summary).to.be.an('object');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.summary.total_sheets).to.be.a('number');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.summary.total_test_cases).to.be.a('number');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has sheets array', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.sheets).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Each sheet has required fields', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    json.sheets.forEach(function(sheet) {",
                  "        pm.expect(sheet.sheet_name).to.be.a('string');",
                  "        pm.expect(sheet.metadata).to.be.an('object');",
                  "        pm.expect(sheet.summary).to.be.an('object');",
                  "        pm.expect(sheet.test_cases).to.be.an('array');",
                  "    });",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.environment.set('last_validation_status', pm.response.json().status);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Validate — Choose Sheets via Form Field (JSON)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Request-ID",
                "value": "postman-{{$randomUUID}}"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "{{sit_file_path}}",
                  "description": "The SIT Excel file (.xlsx)."
                },
                {
                  "key": "sheets",
                  "value": "{{sheet_filter}}",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Comma-separated sheet names to validate (e.g. 'Interbank Transfer,QR MPM'). Set sheet_filter in the environment, or run 02—Discover Sheets first to populate it automatically."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/validate",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "{{api_version}}", "validate"]
            },
            "description": "Validates only the sheets listed in the `sheets` **form field**.\n\nThis is the recommended way to filter sheets: first call `POST /api/v1/sheets` to discover the available sheet names, then supply the chosen names here as a comma-separated form field value.\n\nThe `sheets` field can also be passed as a query string parameter (`?sheets=Sheet1,Sheet2`); if both are present the form field takes precedence."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Only requested sheets are in the response', function () {",
                  "    var filter = pm.environment.get('sheet_filter');",
                  "    if (!filter) return;",
                  "    var requested = filter.split(',').map(function(s) { return s.trim(); });",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    json.sheets.forEach(function(sheet) {",
                  "        pm.expect(requested).to.include(sheet.sheet_name);",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Validate — Choose Sheets via Query String (JSON)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "{{sit_file_path}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/validate?sheets={{sheet_filter}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "{{api_version}}", "validate"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "sheets",
                  "value": "{{sheet_filter}}",
                  "description": "Comma-separated sheet names (e.g. 'Interbank Transfer,QR MPM')."
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Alternative: pass `sheets` as a query string parameter instead of a form field.\n\nBoth approaches produce identical results. The form field (previous request) is preferred for programmatic use; the query string is convenient for quick manual testing."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "04 — Validate (Excel response)",
      "description": "Upload a SIT Excel file and download an annotated workbook with a Validation Result column added per sheet.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Validate — Download Annotated Excel (All Sheets)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Request-ID",
                "value": "postman-{{$randomUUID}}"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "{{sit_file_path}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/validate?format=excel",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "{{api_version}}", "validate"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "format",
                  "value": "excel",
                  "description": "Return an annotated .xlsx file instead of JSON."
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns an annotated `.xlsx` file.\n\nFor each product sheet the service appends a **Validation Result** column (column I):\n- ✓ OK rows are highlighted **green**\n- Rows with issues show the issue text joined by ` | ` and are highlighted **red**\n- Missing metadata cells are highlighted **red**\n\nIn Postman, click **Save Response → Save to a file** to download the annotated workbook."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 — Annotated xlsx",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                {"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet"},
                {"key": "Content-Disposition", "value": "attachment; filename=\"sit_validation_report.xlsx\""}
              ],
              "body": "",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "text"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Content-Type is xlsx', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type'))",
                  "        .to.include('application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Content-Disposition is attachment', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Disposition'))",
                  "        .to.include('attachment');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Validate — Choose Sheets + Excel Output",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "{{sit_file_path}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "sheets",
                  "value": "{{sheet_filter}}",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Comma-separated sheet names to include in the annotated report."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/validate?format=excel",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "{{api_version}}", "validate"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "format", "value": "excel"}
              ]
            },
            "description": "Combines sheet selection (via form field) with Excel output. Only the specified sheets are validated and annotated in the returned workbook."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Content-Type is xlsx', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type'))",
                  "        .to.include('application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "05 — Error Cases",
      "description": "Requests that exercise the documented error responses. Use these to verify the service correctly rejects bad input.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Error — No File Uploaded (400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {"mode": "formdata", "formdata": []},
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/validate",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "{{api_version}}", "validate"]
            },
            "description": "Sends a multipart request with no `file` field.\n\nExpected: `400 Bad Request` with `{\"error\": \"file is required\"}`"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "400 — file is required",
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json; charset=utf-8"}],
              "body": "{\"error\": \"file is required\"}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 400', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(400);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Error message is file is required', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.error).to.eql('file is required');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Error — Wrong File Extension (400)",
